ions,\" <a href=\"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/roman-polanski-prepping-next-feature-715697\">said</a> his producer Robert Benmussa of the forthcoming film. \"But the final decision ultimately depends on the legal security of Roman Polanski in Poland.\"</p><p>He is hoping to make An Officer and a Spy, a biopic of Alfred Dreyfus, a 19th century French officer falsely accused of attempting espionage. He hasn't avoided his native Poland entirely though – he scouted for locations for the film in Krakow and Warsaw, and last year appeared in an unannounced masterclass at the Gdynia film festival.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/jan/17/judge-roman-polanski-rape-case-questioned\">Earlier this year</a> emails leaked to the New York Times revealed that there may have been misconduct by a judge in the original Polanski trial, which, were Polanski to face trial again in the US, could see the director absolved of guilt. But Polanski is clearly not taking any chances.</p><p>His latest film Venus in Fur, starring his wife Emmanuelle Seignier and Mathieu Amalric as an actor and director embroiled in power games, premiered at this year's Cannes film festival. In <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/jun/01/venus-in-fur-review-roman-polanski-sexual-politics\">a four-star Observer review</a>, Jonathan Romney wrote: \"Of all Polanski's latter-day chamber pieces, this is the liveliest: taut, witty and, while very much a male film, nevertheless a sly dismantling of the sexual politics of performance.\"</p>","headline":"Roman Polanski to film in Poland – as long as he won't be extradited","trailText":"<p>Roman Polanski intends to film his next project in Poland, but only if the government can assure that he won't be extradited to the US on child sex charges</p>","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/7/1/1404205086354/Roman-Polanski-003.jpg","wordcount":"355","commentable":"false","byline":"Ben Beaumont-Thomas","pr