you know where to find me if you still want me.' It's as simple as that really,\" he said.</p><p>Added Brosnan: \"Sylvester Stallone is the one that's given us these wonderful platforms for actors who have and had careers to go play and have fun and to entertain. To bring a bunch of guys together who saved the world, fought the bad guys, and put them all on the same stage, that's crazy good.</p><p>\"It's just about entertainment. Avi is somebody I've heard about and his movies always have big brash entertainment value to them. You can really change the world and that's great, but The Expendables? Yeah, I'd love to do The Expendables. It's just a kick in the pants.\"</p><p>The two Expendables films, starring action icons such as Stallone, Arnold Schwarzenegger, Dolph Lundgren, Jason Statham and Jet Li, have so far have grossed more than $579m at the global box office. A third instalment, The Expendables III, is due to hit cinemas in August. It features Mel Gibson as the main villain and also sees Wesley Snipes, Harrison Ford and Antonio Banderas joining the cast. </p><p><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/apr/14/pierce-brosnan-james-bond-never-good-enough\">Brosnan revealed in April</a> that he did not rate his performances as 007 in four films between 1995 and 2002. \"I have no desire to watch myself as James Bond. 'Cause it's just never good enough,\" he said. \"It's a horrible feeling.\"</p><p><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/mar/19/pierce-brosnan-interview-long-way-down\">• From March 2014: 30 Minutes with Pierce Brosnan</a><br><br></p>","headline":"Pierce Brosnan angling to join next Expendables movie","trailText":"Former Bond star wants to join crew of not-so-young action heroes in next of Sylvester Stallone's series of films","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/7/1/1404205828522/171f1ba8-e055-40ee-b3b5-eab6e0e03086-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"288","commentable":"true","byline":"Ben Child","producti