4 years to be able to share that traumatising experience. That story shocked me to my core. ... I used Disney princesses because it's a visual language that my targeted audience would be attracted to.\" </p><p>The figures used for the campaign <a href=\"http://www.bjs.gov/content/pub/pdf/crv92.pdf\">reportedly cite a 1992 US study</a>. </p><p>Disney has not yet made any public comment on the images, but they have caused outrage and consternation among readers commenting on Yahoo's original story. One wrote: \"Disney needs to sue. This is just plain WRONG - taking beloved classic children's characters and using them like this! I'm even freaked out by this, and I don't even LIKE these movies ... Now when a kid watches these movies they will think of this and it will ruin any good memories they had watching these movies!\"</p><p>Others were more supportive, with one reader commenting: \"I'm glad you're all shocked and upset by these images. The sexual abuse of children should never a comfortable thing to confront.\"</p><p>The artist <a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2672507/Artist-draws-Disney-heroines-kissing-FATHERS-provocative-campaign-fight-child-sexual-abuse-family-members.html#ixzz366Tf29Gb\">told Mail Online</a> she had already received an email from one young woman who had been helped by the campaign. \"I received an email from a girl thanking me for the project and telling me that she decided to report her father after seeing the posters. I actually cried,\" she said. \"You have no idea how glad I am now that I actually published the series. If the posters could change one person's life, then it's worth it.\"</p><p>The actor Angelina Jolie <a href=\"http://www.vanityfair.com/vf-hollywood/angelina-jolie-maleficent-rape\">said recently</a> that a scene in Disney blockbuster fantasy Maleficent, in which the title character is drugged and has her wings cut off, had unusually dark adult overtones for a children's film. \"We were very conscious, the writer [Linda Woolverton] and I, that it was a metaphor for rape,\" she told the BBC.</p>","headline":"Disney heroines kissed by fathers in unauthorised anti-rape campaign","trailText":"<p>A new series of images by artist Saint Hoax shows unhappy clinches between characters in Walt Disney movies to highlight the number of children assaulted by family members</p>","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Arts/Arts_/Pictures/2014/6/3/1401799179124/Angelina-Jolie-in-Malefic-006.jpg","wordcount":"442","commentable":"true","byline":"Ben Child","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-07-03T08:10:07Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/jun/30/disney-images-princess-anti-rape-campaign","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/film/2014/jun/30/disney-images-princess-anti-rape-campaign","tags":[{"id":"film/walt-disney-company","webTitle":"Walt Disney Company","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","sectionName":"Film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/walt-disney-company","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/film/walt-disney-company","references":[]},{"id":"film/film","webTitle":"Film","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","sectionName":"Film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/film","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/film/film","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","webTitle":"Culture","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","sectionName":"Culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/culture","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/culture/culture","references":[]},{"id":"artanddesign/artanddesign","webTitle":"Art and design","type":"keyword","sectionId":"artanddesign","sectionName":"Art and design","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/artanddesign","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/artanddesign/artanddesign","references":[]},{"id":"profile/benchild","webTitle":"Ben Child","r2ContributorId":"24984","type":"contributor","bio":"<p>Ben Child is a journalist, DJ and producer whose main interests lie in the worlds of film and music</p>","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/profile/benchild","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/profile/benchild","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/news","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/tone/news","references":[]},{"id":"society/rape","webTitle":"Rape","type":"keyword","sectionId":"society","sectionName":"Society","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/society/rape","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/society/rape","references":[]},{"id":"type/article","webTitle":"Article","type":"type","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/articles","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/type/article","references":[]}],"references":[],"elements":[{"id":"gu-image-440841338","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Arts/Arts_/Pictures/2014/6/3/1401799185800/Angelina-Jolie-in-Malefic-011.jpg","typeData":{"source":"W Disney/Everett/Rex","altText":"Angelina Jolie in Maleficent","height":"276","credit":"W Disney/Everett/Rex","caption":"Angelina Jolie in Maleficent. The actor has recently said that one scene in the Disney film was intended as a metaphor for rape. Photograph: W Disney/Everett/Rex","width":"460"}}]},{"id":"gu-image-440841339","relation":"thumbnail","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Arts/Arts_/Pictures/2014/6/3/1401799179124/Angelina-Jolie-in-Malefic-006.jpg","typeData":{"source":"W Disney/Everett/Rex","altText":"Angelina Jolie in Maleficent","height":"84","credit":"W Disney/Everett/Rex","caption":"Angelina Jolie in Maleficent. Photograph: W Disney/Everett/Rex","width":"140"}},{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Arts/Arts_/Pictures/2014/6/3/1401799187203/Angelina-J