ulating than the Berningers would have you believe. Invited to join his famous bro on tour, Tom sets about documenting the band's triumphs and his own mishaps: awkward interviews (\"Do you ever get … tired on stage?\"), shambolic backstage chores (\"You've got the towels and water, right?\"), botched guest lists (\"Werner Herzog has been waiting out there for, like, 40 minutes!\"), and a failure to board the tour bus that finally gets him fired. At which point Tom retreats to the safety of the family home, and the film becomes a domestic study of sibling rivalry and support. It's an uneven affair, embraced as unguardedly \"intimate\" by some fans of the band, but in reality less moving than <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2009/feb/22/anvil-music-documentary-review\" title=\"\"><em>Anvil! The Story of Anvil</em></a>, and lacking the objective insight of Terry Zwigoff's oddly comparable <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/movie/53960/crumb\" title=\"\"><em>Crumb</em></a>.</p>","headline":"Mistaken for Strangers review – hamfisted rockumentary","trailText":"<p>An uneven study of the relationship between National rocker Matt Berninger and his brother leaves <strong>Mark Kermode</strong> unmoved</p>","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/6/26/1403790651434/Tom-and-Matt-Berninger-in-004.jpg","wordcount":"179","commentable":"true","starRating":"2","byline":"Mark Kermode, Observer film critic","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-07-26T13:43:00Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/jun/29/mistaken-for-strangers-hamfisted-rockumentary","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/film/2014/jun/29/mistaken-for-strangers-hamfisted-rockumentary","tags":[{"id":"film/music-documentary","webTitle":"Music documentary","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","sectionName":"Film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/music-documentary","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.c